00:51:24,400 --> 00:51:26,920
I'll think a great deal
about what you've said.

767
00:51:40,840 --> 00:51:43,200
Ruby, have you finished
your spelling, love?

768
00:51:59,000 --> 00:52:02,480
Ruby? Ruby?

769
00:52:08,920 --> 00:52:09,800
Ruby?

770
00:52:14,320 --> 00:52:17,640
Ruby? What are you doing, love?

771
00:52:18,680 --> 00:52:20,160
I can hear voices.

772
00:52:21,600 --> 00:52:23,120
Coming from up the chimney.

773
00:52:26,880 --> 00:52:28,040
What voices?

774
00:52:28,120 --> 00:52:29,280
The grey man.

775
00:52:34,520 --> 00:52:35,400
[man] Gentlemen,

776
00:52:35,480 --> 00:52:39,000
Mr Thomas Shelby, Birmingham South.

777
00:52:42,040 --> 00:52:47,320
Mister Speaker, I was raised in a family
that endured living conditions

778
00:52:47,400 --> 00:52:50,200
that would test the morality
of even the most virtuous.

779
00:52:51,480 --> 00:52:55,000
Indeed, even the best of us
would have our virtues

780
00:52:55,080 --> 00:52:58,080
trounced and thwarted
by life and the meanness

781
00:52:58,160 --> 00:53:01,240
and the bitterness
of an overcrowded British slum.

782
00:53:01,320 --> 00:53:03,360
What would you know about virtue?

783
00:53:03,440 --> 00:53:04,960
[clamouring]

784
00:53:10,280 --> 00:53:11,600
[Lizzie] Quickly, please.

785
00:53:11,680 --> 00:53:13,000
[Lizzie breathing heavily]

786
00:53:13,600 --> 00:53:17,120
Therefore, Mister Speaker,
I intend to put before this house

787
00:53:17,200 --> 00:53:22,920
a bill which will offer radical reform
in housing policy in this country,

788
00:53:23,000 --> 00:53:25,040
in which slums are cleared,

789
00:53:25,120 --> 00:53:30,320
new houses are built,
with new standards in health and hygiene.

790
00:53:34,160 --> 00:53:37,040
Westminster 245. House of Commons.

791
00:53:37,600 --> 00:53:39,280
[telephone ringing]

792
00:53:42,160 --> 00:53:44,920
The time has come for change.
The people have had enough.

793
00:53:45,000 --> 00:53:45,880
[giggles]

794
00:53:45,960 --> 00:53:48,760
Let's open the windows, let in new light,

795
00:53:48,840 --> 00:53:53,400
build a new Jerusalem,
brick by government-owned brick.

796
00:53:53,480 --> 00:53:55,360
[all cheering]

797
00:53:59,200 --> 00:54:00,160
Into there.

798
00:54:00,240 --> 00:54:01,160
[Ruby coughing]

799
00:54:04,920 --> 00:54:05,760
Good.

800
00:54:10,600 --> 00:54:11,520
Doctor?

801
00:54:15,600 --> 00:54:17,120
Yeah, Westminster 245.

802
00:54:21,880 --> 00:54:22,800
Mr Shelby.

803
00:54:42,480 --> 00:54:45,800
[Lizzie] "Tickner Maura, O Beng, O Beng,"
<i>over and over again.</i>

804
00:54:45,880 --> 00:54:48,360
-[Michael] <i>How is the family?</i>
-[Polly] <i>One of you will die.</i>

805
00:54:48,440 --> 00:54:51,360
-[Ruby] <i>He's staring at me, Daddy.</i>
-[Lizzie] <i>A man with green eyes.</i>

806
00:54:52,320 --> 00:54:54,120
Can you stop the voices?

807
00:54:55,760 --> 00:54:57,680
[Lizzie] There are no voices, my love.

808
00:54:58,520 --> 00:54:59,800
[Ruby] It's the grey man.

809
00:55:01,200 --> 00:55:02,840
He says he's coming for me.

810
00:55:04,520 --> 00:55:06,360
And he's coming for Daddy as well.

811
00:55:29,920 --> 00:55:32,080
-[man grunts]
-[Tommy gasps]

812
00:55:43,800 --> 00:55:46,040
[telephone ringing]

813
00:55:53,880 --> 00:55:56,080
[both grunting]

814
00:55:56,160 --> 00:55:57,280
[man yells]

815
00:56:07,800 --> 00:56:10,960
-[knife pierces]
-[screams]

816
00:56:19,120 --> 00:56:20,520
[knock on door]

817
00:56:20,600 --> 00:56:21,880
[man] Mr Shelby?

818
00:56:22,920 --> 00:56:25,080
Is everything all right in there?

819
00:56:27,160 --> 00:56:28,000
[knocking continues]

820
00:56:28,080 --> 00:56:29,120
Mr Shelby?

821
00:56:29,920 --> 00:56:33,480
Everything's fine. Everything's fine.

822
00:56:35,240 --> 00:56:37,240
[telephone ringing]

823
00:56:46,440 --> 00:56:47,800
-Hello?
-[Lizzie] <i>Tommy?</i>

824
00:56:47,880 --> 00:56:50,800
Tommy. She has a temperature
of 101 and nothing is working.

825
00:56:50,880 --> 00:56:52,760
-Just get here now.
<i>-Lizzie?</i>

826
00:56:52,840 --> 00:56:54,160
-Please.
<i>-Lizzie...</i>

827
00:56:56,440 --> 00:56:57,560
[sighs]

828
00:56:59,400 --> 00:57:02,600
[breathes heavily]

829
00:57:18,280 --> 00:57:19,160
Where is she?

830
00:57:19,240 --> 00:57:20,800
She's with the doctor upstairs.

831
00:57:23,440 --> 00:57:24,480
Listen, Tommy.

832
00:57:25,760 --> 00:57:28,080
He said we shouldn't
come close to her in case...

833
00:57:28,160 --> 00:57:29,160
In case of what?

834
00:57:30,160 --> 00:57:31,760
When she coughs, there's blood.

835
00:57:49,840 --> 00:57:56,360
Madonna, put me through to the number
I gave you for Esme Shelby-Lee.

